Deep Breath		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:You can hold your breath for %1 rounds before you must start making  Constitution checks.|CON*3																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.24
Drink for Free	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:You are admired or feared in the taverns you frequent. You can designate %1 taverns as “favored taverns". When in a favored tavern, you drink for free. In addition, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus on Diplomacy and Intimidate checks within a favored tavern.|CL																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.24
Farseer		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:Pirates take turns serving as lookouts. You reduce any distance-based penalties on Perception checks by half when you are at least 10 feet off the ground or above the deck of a ship.																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.24
Hand Stab		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:You can weaken an opponent's weapon hand by hitting with a sneak attack. When you deals sneak attack damage against an opponent, that opponent becomes easier to disarm. Until the end of your next turn, anyone attempting to disarm that opponent gains a +2 bonus on the disarm attempt.																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.24
Quick Appraise	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:You must at times quickly select the most valuable items to spirit away. You can appraises an item as a move action and can determine the most valuable item in a treasure hoard as a standard action.																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.24
Rigging Monkey	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:Some pirates become skilled at climbing on ropes and rigging. You gain a +2 bonus on Climb checks when using a rope to help you climb. In addition, when using a rope to help you climb, you can move at half your speed. (By accepting a –5 penalty you can move at your normal speed.)																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.24
Storm Sailor	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:You treat all storms as if they were one category less severe for the purposes of sailing and navigation. (This benefit stacks with the Hurricane Savvy character trait and other effects related to wind conditions.) You can make an Acrobatics check to move your normal speed across uneven ground, and you do not take a penalty on any Acrobatics checks due to slightly slippery, slightly  unsteady, or moderately unsteady conditions.																																SOURCEPAGE:p.25
Windrigger		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.PirateTrick	DESC:You have learned the tricky art of tacking. With a DC 15 Profession (sailor) check, you increase your ship's base movement by 5 feet for 1 hour.																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.25

